BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260626T110610Z
UID:bwnp-x3ixm04f5wj7-ev-s72ne-20260422180000
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260422T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260422T210000
DESCRIPTION:Have a piece of clothing that isn't getting as much of your att
 ention or love anymore? Have something with imperfections you want to hide
 ? Holes\, rips\, snags\, or tears in your clothing? This is the workshop f
 or you!\nWe have a bunch of fabric samples that would be great for upcycli
 ng\, patches and other mending endeavors. We'll have community members the
 re to help you with your projects and instruct or guide you on the best wa
 y to complete your goal.\nNote: We will not be completing your projects fo
 r you\, we want you to learn how to! This workshop is for people who want 
 to be the one mending and sewing (we will help you if it's needed\, of cou
 rse).\nBring your unloved item and let's transform it into something you'r
 e obsessed with! Fabric and supplies will be provided but feel free to bri
 ng your own if you have a project in mind!\n\n\nhttps://bookwhen.com/sequo
 iafabrica/e/ev-s72ne-20260422180000
LOCATION:1736 18th Street\, San Francisco CA 94107-2343
ORGANIZER:mailto:info@sequoiafabrica.org
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Upmending (upcycling + mending) Social
URL;VALUE=URI:https://bookwhen.com/sequoiafabrica/e/ev-s72ne-20260422180000
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260626T110610Z
UID:bwnp-x3ixm04f5wj7-ev-s6ptb-20260423180000
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260423T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260423T200000
DESCRIPTION:Whether you are an experienced printmaker\, or new to the craft
 \, join us in the workshop for an evening to socialize\, meet other makers
 \, make some messes\, and hopefully some art 🎨🧑‍🎨!\nThis casual
  event will give you the opportunity to flex your creative muscles. We wil
 l have supplies and materials available for experimenting\, and bringing y
 our ideas to life.\nDon't know where to start or what to make? We also hav
 e prefabricated stamps as examples for you to practice printing with.\nThi
 s event is primarily focused on block prints\, which is a type of relief p
 rintmaking (https://ldart.work/printing-relief-techniques-parts-1-to-7/).\
 nThis social often has a waiting list. Please cancel your ticket if you ar
 e not able to attend in order to make room for another student.\n\n\nhttps
 ://bookwhen.com/sequoiafabrica/e/ev-s6ptb-20260423180000
LOCATION:1736 18th Street\, San Francisco CA 94107-2343
ORGANIZER:mailto:info@sequoiafabrica.org
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Block Printmaking Social
URL;VALUE=URI:https://bookwhen.com/sequoiafabrica/e/ev-s6ptb-20260423180000
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260626T110610Z
UID:bwnp-x3ixm04f5wj7-ev-sjqfp-20260425153000
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260425T153000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260425T183000
DESCRIPTION:New to Cricut and not sure where to start? This beginner-friend
 ly workshop is designed to walk\nyou step-by-step through the entire proce
 ss of creating a personalized vinyl tumbler—from\nsetting up your machin
 e to applying your final design.\nUsing a guided\, hands-on approach\, you
 ’ll learn how to navigate Cricut Design Space\, choose\nthe right tools 
 and materials\, and confidently complete your first project. This class br
 eaks\neverything down into simple\, manageable steps so you don’t feel o
 verwhelmed.\nBy the end of class\, you’ll leave with a custom tumbler an
 d the confidence to keep creating at\nhome.\n\n\nhttps://bookwhen.com/sequ
 oiafabrica/e/ev-sjqfp-20260425153000
LOCATION:1736 18th Street\, San Francisco CA 94107-2343
ORGANIZER:mailto:info@sequoiafabrica.org
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Cricut Beginner Workshop: Design & Create a Personalized Vinyl Tumb
 ler
URL;VALUE=URI:https://bookwhen.com/sequoiafabrica/e/ev-sjqfp-20260425153000
END:VEVENT
