DESCRIPTION:This time is set aside for volunteers (or the volunteer-curious
 ) to come to Sequoia Fabrica and get help from the Volunteer Coordinator. 
 New volunteer applicants are expected to attend the volunteer office hour 
 after their orientation.\nNOTE: You are encouraged to sign up for this eve
 nt in advance! If no one is in attendance 10 min into the office hours\, t
 he event will be considered cancelled so our volunteer coordinator can go 
 home ✌️.\nIf you have any questions you can always email us (mailto://
 info@sequoiafabrica.org).\n\n\nhttps://bookwhen.com/sequoiafabrica/e/ev-sy
 f1-20260602200000
LOCATION:1736 18th Street\, San Francisco CA 94107-2343
ORGANIZER:mailto:info@sequoiafabrica.org
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Volunteer Office Hours
URL;VALUE=URI:https://bookwhen.com/sequoiafabrica/e/ev-syf1-20260602200000
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260626T110611Z
UID:bwnp-x3ixm04f5wj7-ev-su54q-20260611190000
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260611T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260611T210000
DESCRIPTION:Join us for an evening of hand embroidery and chit chat. The 
 event is open for experienced embroiderers and those who have never/or sel
 dom picked up a needle. If you’re new to embroidery\, we have a simple
  stitch sampler and supplies that we can use to cover some basic stitches 
 like the running stitch\, back stitch\, chain stitch\, French knots or mak
 e your own sashiko square. If you have questions on a project bring them a
 long\, we’ll try our best to answer them.\n\n\nhttps://bookwhen.com/sequ
 oiafabrica/e/ev-su54q-20260611190000
LOCATION:1736 18th Street\, San Francisco CA 94107-2343
ORGANIZER:mailto:info@sequoiafabrica.org
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Hand Embroidery Social
URL;VALUE=URI:https://bookwhen.com/sequoiafabrica/e/ev-su54q-20260611190000
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260626T110611Z
UID:bwnp-x3ixm04f5wj7-ev-shktc-20260615180000
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260615T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260615T210000
DESCRIPTION:Have a piece of clothing that isn't getting as much of your att
 ention or love anymore? Have something with imperfections you want to hide
 ? Holes\, rips\, snags\, or tears in your clothing? This is the workshop f
 or you!\nWe have a bunch of fabric samples that would be great for upcycli
 ng\, patches and other mending endeavors. We'll have community members the
 re to help you with your projects and instruct or guide you on the best wa
 y to complete your goal.\nNote: We will not be completing your projects fo
 r you\, we want you to learn how to! This workshop is for people who want 
 to be the one mending and sewing (we will help you if it's needed\, of cou
 rse).\nBring your unloved item and let's transform it into something you'r
 e obsessed with! Fabric and supplies will be provided but feel free to bri
 ng your own if you have a project in mind!\n\n\nhttps://bookwhen.com/sequo
 iafabrica/e/ev-shktc-20260615180000
LOCATION:1736 18th Street\, San Francisco CA 94107-2343
ORGANIZER:mailto:info@sequoiafabrica.org
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Upmending (upcycling + mending) Social
URL;VALUE=URI:https://bookwhen.com/sequoiafabrica/e/ev-shktc-20260615180000
END:VEVENT
